article.headline: Fairfield 82, American U. 73
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Jonathan Han scored 20 points to lead Fairfield to an 83-73 victory over American on Saturday. Warren Edney added 15 points and Herbie Allen had 13 for the Stags (3-3), who made 11 of 18 3-point attempts and also made 35 trips to the free throw line, making 23 of them. American led early before Fairfield used a 9-0 run to take the lead. The teams wound up tied at 40 at halftime, before Faifield pulled away after hte break. Garrison Carr scored 19 points and Brian Gilmore had 16 for American (4-2).
